<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7340963>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Neotype slide of Crisicoccus seruratus (Kanda 1933). The neotype is indicated by a black arrow." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7340963/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7340965>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Crisicoccus seruratus (Kanda 1933), adult female collected in Kasama, Ibaraki prefecture, Japan in 2022. ALC, anal lobe cerarius; ANT, antenna; DP, discoidal pore; DS, dorsal seta; LG, hind tibia, tarsus and claw; MP, multilocular disc pore; OCD I, large type oral collar duct; OCD II, small type oral collar duct; PLC, penultimate cerarius (C17); TP, trilocular pore; VS, ventral seta. Scale bars: 200 µm for ANT and LG; 50 µm for ALC, PLC and VS; 10 µm for others." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7340965/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

